{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As you pointed out, every time you come here, you learn something."},{"time":4000,"text":"This morning, the world's experts"},{"time":6000,"text":"from I guess three or four different companies on building seats,"},{"time":10000,"text":"I think concluded that ultimately, the solution is, people shouldn't sit down."},{"time":15000,"text":"I could have told them that."},{"time":17000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":19000,"text":"Yesterday, the automotive guys gave us some new insights."},{"time":25000,"text":"They pointed out that, I believe it was between 30 and 50 years from today,"},{"time":31000,"text":"they will be steering cars by wire,"},{"time":34000,"text":"without all that mechanical stuff."},{"time":36000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":38000,"text":"That's reassuring."},{"time":40000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":44000,"text":"They then pointed out that there'd be, sort of, the other controls by wire,"},{"time":49000,"text":"to get rid of all that mechanical stuff."},{"time":51000,"text":"That's pretty good, but why not get rid of the wires?"},{"time":56000,"text":"Then you don't need anything to control the car, except thinking about it."},{"time":64000,"text":"I would love to talk about the technology,"},{"time":66000,"text":"and sometime, in what's past the 15 minutes,"},{"time":70000,"text":"I'll be happy to talk to all the techno-geeks around here"},{"time":72000,"text":"about what's in here."},{"time":76000,"text":"But if I had one thing to say about this, before we get to first,"},{"time":80000,"text":"it would be that from the time we started building this,"},{"time":86000,"text":"the big idea wasn't the technology."},{"time":88000,"text":"It really was a big idea in technology when we started applying it"},{"time":91000,"text":"in the iBOT for the disabled community."},{"time":93000,"text":"The big idea here is, I think, a new piece of a solution"},{"time":99000,"text":"to a fairly big problem in transportation."},{"time":103000,"text":"And maybe to put that in perspective: there's so much data on this,"},{"time":108000,"text":"I'll be happy to give it to you in different forms."},{"time":110000,"text":"You never know what strikes the fancy of whom,"},{"time":113000,"text":"but everybody is perfectly willing to believe the car changed the world."},{"time":118000,"text":"And Henry Ford, just about 100 years ago, started cranking out Model Ts."},{"time":122000,"text":"What I don't think most people think about"},{"time":124000,"text":"is the context of how technology is applied."},{"time":128000,"text":"For instance, in that time, 91 percent of America"},{"time":131000,"text":"lived either on farms or in small towns."},{"time":134000,"text":"So, the car --"},{"time":137000,"text":"the horseless carriage that replaced the horse and carriage -- was a big deal;"},{"time":141000,"text":"it went twice as fast as a horse and carriage."},{"time":143000,"text":"It was half as long."},{"time":145000,"text":"And it was an environmental improvement, because, for instance,"},{"time":149000,"text":"in 1903 they outlawed horses and buggies in downtown Manhattan,"},{"time":154000,"text":"because you can imagine what the roads look like"},{"time":157000,"text":"when you have a million horses,"},{"time":160000,"text":"and a million of them urinating and doing other things,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and the typhoid and other problems created were almost unimaginable."},{"time":170000,"text":"So the car was the clean environmental alternative to a horse and buggy."},{"time":174000,"text":"It also was a way for people to get from their farm to a farm,"},{"time":178000,"text":"or their farm to a town, or from a town to a city."},{"time":181000,"text":"It all made sense, with 91 percent of the people living there."},{"time":186000,"text":"By the 1950s, we started connecting all the towns together"},{"time":190000,"text":"with what a lot of people claim is the eighth wonder of the world, the highway system."},{"time":194000,"text":"And it is certainly a wonder."},{"time":197000,"text":"And by the way, as I take shots at old technologies,"},{"time":201000,"text":"I want to assure everybody, and particularly the automotive industry --"},{"time":205000,"text":"who's been very supportive of us --"},{"time":207000,"text":"that I don't think this in any way competes with airplanes, or cars."},{"time":215000,"text":"But think about where the world is today."},{"time":219000,"text":"50 percent of the global population now lives in cities."},{"time":222000,"text":"That's 3.2 billion people."},{"time":226000,"text":"We've solved all the transportation problems"},{"time":228000,"text":"that have changed the world to get it to where we are today."},{"time":231000,"text":"500 years ago, sailing ships started getting reliable enough;"},{"time":234000,"text":"we found a new continent."},{"time":236000,"text":"150 years ago, locomotives got efficient enough, steam power,"},{"time":240000,"text":"that we turned the continent into a country."},{"time":243000,"text":"Over the last hundred years, we started building cars,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and then over the 50 years we've connected every city to every other city"},{"time":249000,"text":"in an extraordinarily efficient way,"},{"time":251000,"text":"and we have a very high standard of living as a consequence of that."},{"time":254000,"text":"But during that entire process, more and more people have been born,"},{"time":259000,"text":"and more and more people are moving to cities."},{"time":261000,"text":"China alone is going to move four to six hundred million people"},{"time":265000,"text":"into cities in the next decade and a half."},{"time":269000,"text":"And so, nobody, I think, would argue that airplanes, in the last 50 years,"},{"time":275000,"text":"have turned the continent and the country now into a neighborhood."},{"time":279000,"text":"And if you just look at how technology has been applied,"},{"time":281000,"text":"we've solved all the long-range, high-speed, high-volume,"},{"time":285000,"text":"large-weight problems of moving things around."},{"time":288000,"text":"Nobody would want to give them up."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I certainly wouldn't want to give up my airplane,"},{"time":293000,"text":"or my helicopter, or my Humvee, or my Porsche."},{"time":297000,"text":"I love them all. I don't keep any of them in my living room."},{"time":300000,"text":"The fact is, the last mile is the problem,"},{"time":305000,"text":"and half the world now lives in dense cities."},{"time":308000,"text":"And people spend, depending on who they are,"},{"time":310000,"text":"between 90 and 95 percent of their energy getting around on foot."},{"time":315000,"text":"I think there's -- I don't know what data would impress you,"},{"time":318000,"text":"but how about, 43 percent of the refined fuel produced in the world"},{"time":324000,"text":"is consumed by cars in metropolitan areas in the United States."},{"time":330000,"text":"Three million people die every year in cities due to bad air,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and almost all particulate pollution on this planet"},{"time":338000,"text":"is produced by transportation devices, particularly sitting in cities."},{"time":343000,"text":"And again, I say that not to attack any industry,"},{"time":347000,"text":"I think -- I really do -- I love my airplane,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and cars on highways moving 60 miles an hour"},{"time":353000,"text":"are extraordinarily efficient,"},{"time":355000,"text":"both from an engineering point of view,"},{"time":358000,"text":"an energy consumption point of view, and a utility point of view."},{"time":361000,"text":"And we all love our cars, and I do."},{"time":364000,"text":"The problem is, you get into the city and you want to go four blocks,"},{"time":368000,"text":"it's neither fun nor efficient nor productive."},{"time":371000,"text":"It's not sustainable."},{"time":373000,"text":"If -- in China, in the year 1998, 417 million people used bicycles;"},{"time":379000,"text":"1.7 million people used cars."},{"time":383000,"text":"If five percent of that population became, quote, middle class,"},{"time":387000,"text":"and wanted to go the way we've gone in the last hundred years"},{"time":392000,"text":"at the same time that 50 percent of their population are moving into cities"},{"time":395000,"text":"of the size and density of Manhattan, every six weeks --"},{"time":399000,"text":"it isn't sustainable environmentally;"},{"time":401000,"text":"it isn't sustainable economically -- there just ain't enough oil --"},{"time":405000,"text":"and it's not sustainable politically."},{"time":407000,"text":"I mean, what are we fighting over right now?"},{"time":409000,"text":"We can make it complicated, but what's the world fighting over right now?"},{"time":413000,"text":"So it seemed to me that somebody had to work on that last mile,"},{"time":420000,"text":"and it was dumb luck. We were working on iBOTs,"},{"time":423000,"text":"but once we made this, we instantly decided"},{"time":425000,"text":"it could be a great alternative to jet skis. You don't need the water."},{"time":429000,"text":"Or snowmobiles. You don't need the snow."},{"time":431000,"text":"Or skiing. It's just fun, and people love to move around doing fun things."},{"time":438000,"text":"And every one of those industries, by the way --"},{"time":440000,"text":"just golf carts alone is a multi-billion-dollar industry."},{"time":443000,"text":"But rather than go license this off, which is what we normally do,"},{"time":446000,"text":"it seemed to me that if we put all our effort not into the technology,"},{"time":450000,"text":"but into an understanding of a world that's solved all its other problems,"},{"time":454000,"text":"but has somehow come to accept that cities -- which,"},{"time":459000,"text":"right back from ancient Greece on, were meant to walk around,"},{"time":462000,"text":"cities that were architected and built for people --"},{"time":465000,"text":"now have a footprint that,"},{"time":467000,"text":"while we've solved every other transportation problem --"},{"time":469000,"text":"and it's like Moore's law."},{"time":471000,"text":"I mean, look at the time it took to cross a continent in a Conestoga wagon,"},{"time":476000,"text":"then on a railroad, then an airplane."},{"time":479000,"text":"Every other form of transportation's been improved."},{"time":483000,"text":"In 5,000 years, we've gone backwards in getting around cities."},{"time":487000,"text":"They've gotten bigger; they're spread out."},{"time":490000,"text":"The most expensive real estate on this planet in every city --"},{"time":495000,"text":"Wilshire Boulevard, or Fifth Avenue, or Tokyo, or Paris --"},{"time":499000,"text":"the most expensive real estate is their downtowns."},{"time":502000,"text":"65 percent of the landmass of our cities are parked cars."},{"time":506000,"text":"The 20 largest cities in the world."},{"time":508000,"text":"So you wonder, what if cities could give to their pedestrians"},{"time":513000,"text":"what we take for granted as we now go between cities?"},{"time":517000,"text":"What if you could make them fun, attractive, clean,"},{"time":521000,"text":"environmentally friendly?"},{"time":525000,"text":"What if it would make it a little bit more palatable"},{"time":528000,"text":"to have access via this, as that last link to mass transit,"},{"time":534000,"text":"to get out to your cars so we can all live in the suburbs"},{"time":537000,"text":"and use our cars the way we want,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and then have our cities energized again?"},{"time":544000,"text":"We thought it would be really neat to do that,"},{"time":546000,"text":"and one of the problems we really were worried about"},{"time":548000,"text":"is: how do we get legal on the sidewalk?"},{"time":551000,"text":"Because technically I've got motors; I've got wheels -- I'm a motor vehicle."},{"time":555000,"text":"I don't look like a motor vehicle."},{"time":557000,"text":"I have the same footprint as a pedestrian;"},{"time":559000,"text":"I have the same unique capability"},{"time":563000,"text":"to deal with other pedestrians in a crowded space."},{"time":565000,"text":"I took this down to Ground Zero,"},{"time":567000,"text":"and knocked my way through crowds for an hour."},{"time":570000,"text":"I'm a pedestrian. But the law typically lags technology by a generation or two,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and if we get told we don't belong on the sidewalk, we have two choices."},{"time":581000,"text":"We're a recreational vehicle that doesn't really matter,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and I don't spend my time doing that kind of stuff."},{"time":588000,"text":"Or maybe we should be out in the street"},{"time":590000,"text":"in front of a Greyhound bus or a vehicle."},{"time":594000,"text":"We've been so concerned about that,"},{"time":596000,"text":"we went to the Postmaster General of the United States,"},{"time":598000,"text":"as the first person we ever showed on the outside,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and said, \"Put your people on it. Everybody trusts their postman."},{"time":605000,"text":"And they belong on the sidewalks, and they'll use it seriously.\""},{"time":610000,"text":"He agreed. We went to a number of police departments"},{"time":613000,"text":"that want their police officers back in the neighborhood"},{"time":615000,"text":"on the beat, carrying 70 pounds of stuff. They love it."},{"time":619000,"text":"And I can't believe a policeman is going to give themselves a ticket."},{"time":623000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":626000,"text":"So we've been working really, really hard,"},{"time":628000,"text":"but we knew that the technology would not be as hard to develop"},{"time":631000,"text":"as an attitude about what's important, and how to apply the technology."},{"time":636000,"text":"We went out and we found some visionary people"},{"time":639000,"text":"with enough money to let us design and build these things,"},{"time":644000,"text":"and in hopefully enough time to get them accepted."},{"time":648000,"text":"So, I'm happy, really, I am happy to talk about this technology as much as you want."},{"time":653000,"text":"And yes, it's really fun, and yes, you should all go out and try it."},{"time":657000,"text":"But if I could ask you to do one thing,"},{"time":659000,"text":"it's not to think about it as a piece of technology,"},{"time":661000,"text":"but just imagine that, although we all understand somehow"},{"time":665000,"text":"that it's reasonable that we use our 4,000-pound machine,"},{"time":669000,"text":"which can go 60 miles an hour,"},{"time":671000,"text":"that can bring you everywhere you want to go,"},{"time":673000,"text":"and somehow it's also what we used for the last mile,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and it's broken, and it doesn't work."},{"time":682000,"text":"One of the more exciting things that occurred to us"},{"time":685000,"text":"about why it might get accepted, happened out here in California."},{"time":690000,"text":"A few weeks ago, after we launched it,"},{"time":692000,"text":"we were here with a news crew on Venice Beach, zipping up and back,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and he's marveling at the technology,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and meanwhile bicycles are zipping by,"},{"time":701000,"text":"and skateboarders are zipping by,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and a little old lady -- I mean, if you looked in the dictionary,"},{"time":707000,"text":"a little old lady -- came by me --"},{"time":710000,"text":"and now that I'm on this, I'm the height of a normal adult now --"},{"time":714000,"text":"and she just stops, and the camera is there, and she looks up at me"},{"time":720000,"text":"and says, \"Can I try that?\""},{"time":723000,"text":"And what was I -- you know, how are you going to say anything?"},{"time":726000,"text":"And so I said, \"Sure.\""},{"time":728000,"text":"So I get off, and she gets on, and with a little bit of the usual, ah,"},{"time":734000,"text":"then she turns around, and she goes about 20 feet,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and she turns back around, and she's all smiles."},{"time":742000,"text":"And she comes back to me and she stops, and she says,"},{"time":748000,"text":"\"Finally, they made something for us.\""},{"time":752000,"text":"And the camera is looking down at her."},{"time":754000,"text":"I'm thinking, \"Wow, that was great --"},{"time":756000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":757000,"text":"-- please lady, don't say another word.\""},{"time":759000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":762000,"text":"And the camera is down at her,"},{"time":764000,"text":"and this guy has to put the microphone in her face,"},{"time":766000,"text":"said, \"What do you mean by that?\""},{"time":768000,"text":"And I figured, \"It's all over now,\""},{"time":770000,"text":"and she looks up and she says, \"Well,\""},{"time":774000,"text":"she's still watching these guys go; she says, \"I can't ride a bike,\" no,"},{"time":777000,"text":"she says, \"I can't use a skateboard, and I've never used roller blades,\""},{"time":781000,"text":"she knew them by name;"},{"time":783000,"text":"she says, \"And it's been 50 years since I rode a bicycle.\""},{"time":786000,"text":"Then she looks up, she's looking up, and she says,"},{"time":790000,"text":"\"And I'm 81 years old, and I don't drive a car anymore."},{"time":794000,"text":"I still have to get to the store, and I can't carry a lot of things.\""},{"time":798000,"text":"And it suddenly occurred to me, that among my many fears,"},{"time":802000,"text":"were not just that the bureaucracy and the regulators"},{"time":805000,"text":"and the legislators might not get it --"},{"time":808000,"text":"it was that, fundamentally, you believe there's pressure among the people"},{"time":813000,"text":"not to invade the most precious little bit of space left,"},{"time":816000,"text":"the sidewalks in these cities."},{"time":818000,"text":"When you look at the 36 inches of legal requirement for sidewalk,"},{"time":822000,"text":"then the eight foot for the parked car, then the three lanes,"},{"time":825000,"text":"and then the other eight feet -- it's --"},{"time":827000,"text":"that little piece is all that's there."},{"time":831000,"text":"But she looks up and says this,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and it occurs to me, well, kids aren't going to mind these things,"},{"time":835000,"text":"and they don't vote, and business people and then young adults"},{"time":839000,"text":"aren't going to mind these things -- they're pretty cool --"},{"time":841000,"text":"so I guess subliminally I was worried"},{"time":843000,"text":"that it's the older population that's going to worry."},{"time":846000,"text":"So, having seen this, and having worried about it for eight years,"},{"time":851000,"text":"the first thing I do is pick up my phone and ask our marketing and regulatory guys,"},{"time":855000,"text":"call AARP, get an appointment right away."},{"time":858000,"text":"We've got to show them this thing."},{"time":860000,"text":"And they took it to Washington; they showed them;"},{"time":863000,"text":"and they're going to be involved now,"},{"time":865000,"text":"watching how these things get absorbed in a number of cities,"},{"time":869000,"text":"like Atlanta, where we're doing trials to see if it really can, in fact,"},{"time":873000,"text":"help re-energize their downtown."},{"time":876000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":883000,"text":"The bottom line is, whether you believe the United Nations,"},{"time":888000,"text":"or any of the other think tanks --"},{"time":890000,"text":"in the next 20 years, all human population growth on this planet"},{"time":894000,"text":"will be in cities."},{"time":896000,"text":"In Asia alone, it will be over a billion people."},{"time":899000,"text":"They learned to start with cell phones."},{"time":903000,"text":"They didn't have to take the 100-year trip we took."},{"time":906000,"text":"They start at the top of the technology food chain."},{"time":909000,"text":"We've got to start building cities and human environments"},{"time":912000,"text":"where a 150-pound person can go a couple of miles"},{"time":915000,"text":"in a dense, rich, green-space environment,"},{"time":918000,"text":"without being in a 4,000-pound machine to do it."},{"time":922000,"text":"Cars were not meant for parallel parking;"},{"time":925000,"text":"they're wonderful machines to go between cities, but just think about it:"},{"time":929000,"text":"we've solved all the long-range, high-speed problems."},{"time":934000,"text":"The Greeks went from the theater of Dionysus to the Parthenon in their sandals."},{"time":939000,"text":"You do it in your sneakers."},{"time":941000,"text":"Not much has changed."},{"time":943000,"text":"If this thing goes only three times as fast as walking -- three times --"},{"time":948000,"text":"a 30-minute walk becomes 10 minutes."},{"time":950000,"text":"Your choice, when living in a city, if it's now 10 minutes --"},{"time":955000,"text":"because at 30 minutes you want an alternative, whether it's a bus, a train --"},{"time":959000,"text":"we've got to build an infrastructure -- a light rail --"},{"time":961000,"text":"or you're going to keep parking those cars."},{"time":963000,"text":"But if you could put a pin in most cities,"},{"time":966000,"text":"and imagine how far you could, if you had the time, walk in one half-hour, it's the city."},{"time":972000,"text":"If you could make it fun, and make it eight or 10 minutes,"},{"time":974000,"text":"you can't find your car, un-park your car, move your car,"},{"time":977000,"text":"re-park your car and go somewhere;"},{"time":979000,"text":"you can't get to a cab or a subway."},{"time":982000,"text":"We could change the way people allocate their resources,"},{"time":985000,"text":"the way this planet uses its energy,"},{"time":988000,"text":"make it more fun."},{"time":990000,"text":"And we're hoping to some extent history will say we were right."},{"time":995000,"text":"That's Segway. This is a Stirling cycle engine;"},{"time":998000,"text":"this had been confused by a lot of things we're doing."},{"time":1002000,"text":"This little beast, right now, is producing a few hundred watts of electricity."},{"time":1007000,"text":"Yes, it could be attached to this,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and yes, on a kilogram of propane,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"you could drive from New York to Boston if you so choose."},{"time":1017000,"text":"Perhaps more interesting about this little engine is it'll burn any fuel,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"because some of you might be skeptical"},{"time":1023000,"text":"about the capability of this to have an impact,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"where most of the world you can't simply plug into your 120-volt outlet."},{"time":1031000,"text":"We've been working on this,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"actually, as an alternative energy source,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"starting way back with Johnson &amp; Johnson, to run an iBOT,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"because the best batteries you could get --"},{"time":1041000,"text":"10 watt-hours per kilogram in lead,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"20 watt-hours per kilogram nickel-cadmium,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"40 watt-hours per kilogram in nickel-metal hydride,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"60 watt-hours per kilogram in lithium,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"8,750 watt-hours of energy in every kilogram of propane or gasoline --"},{"time":1055000,"text":"which is why nobody drives electric cars."},{"time":1057000,"text":"But, in any event, if you can burn it with the same efficiency --"},{"time":1063000,"text":"because it's external combustion -- as your kitchen stove,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"if you can burn any fuel, it turns out to be pretty neat."},{"time":1069000,"text":"It makes just enough electricity to, for instance, do this,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"which at night is enough electricity, in the rest of the world,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"as Mr. Holly -- Dr. Holly -- pointed out,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"can run computers and a light bulb."},{"time":1081000,"text":"But more interestingly, the thermodynamics of this say,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"you're never going to get more than 20 percent efficiency."},{"time":1088000,"text":"It doesn't matter much -- it says if you get 200 watts of electricity,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"you'll get 700 or 800 watts of heat."},{"time":1094000,"text":"If you wanted to boil water and re-condense it at a rate of 10 gallons an hour,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"it takes about 25, a little over 25.3 kilowatt --"},{"time":1102000,"text":"25,000 watts of continuous power -- to do it."},{"time":1106000,"text":"That's so much energy, you couldn't afford to desalinate"},{"time":1108000,"text":"or clean water in this country that way."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Certainly, in the rest of the world, your choice is to devastate the place,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"turning everything that will burn into heat, or drink the water that's available."},{"time":1119000,"text":"The number one cause of death on this planet among humans is bad water."},{"time":1123000,"text":"Depending on whose numbers you believe,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"it's between 60 and 85,000 people per day."},{"time":1128000,"text":"We don't need sophisticated heart transplants around the world."},{"time":1131000,"text":"We need water."},{"time":1133000,"text":"And women shouldn't have to spend four hours a day looking for it,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"or watching their kids die."},{"time":1138000,"text":"We figured out how to put a vapor-compression distiller on this thing,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"with a counter-flow heat exchanger to take the waste heat,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"then using a little bit of the electricity control that process,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"and for 450 watts, which is a little more than half of its waste heat,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"it will make 10 gallons an hour of distilled water"},{"time":1156000,"text":"from anything that comes into it to cool it."},{"time":1158000,"text":"So if we put this box on here in a few years,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"could we have a solution to transportation, electricity,"},{"time":1167000,"text":"and communication, and maybe drinkable water"},{"time":1171000,"text":"in a sustainable package that weighs 60 pounds?"},{"time":1175000,"text":"I don't know, but we'll try it."},{"time":1177000,"text":"I better shut up."},{"time":1179000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}